00:24:27.424 --> 00:24:30.385
They came here on a group tour, and they all shared some gimbap.

00:24:30.386 --> 00:24:32.971
- Where is your discomfort? - Right, well

00:24:36.642 --> 00:24:39.186
You're the doctor who was on TV.

00:24:40.270 --> 00:24:44.024
I was kind of hoping to get examined by a different doctor.

00:24:45.609 --> 00:24:47.819
Uh, I've, uh, got an underlying condition,

00:24:47.820 --> 00:24:50.697
So I'm just worried that something terrible might happen

00:24:50.698 --> 00:24:52.699
If I were to take the wrong meds.

00:24:52.700 --> 00:24:56.494
- Sir, this doctor here is also-- - I-It's okay. It's okay. It's okay.

00:24:56.495 --> 00:24:58.079
I'm an ER doctor. :cue

00:24:58.080 --> 00:25:00.499
If it's all right with you, may I take a look?

00:25:03.335 --> 00:25:04.336
Okay.

00:25:05.212 --> 00:25:06.880
Sir, I'm going to take your pulse.

00:25:08.007 --> 00:25:10.341
You're urinating less or it's gotten darker, right?

00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:13.011
Gosh  everything I drink just passes right through me.

00:25:13.012 --> 00:25:15.847
He's going to be dehydrated. Prep an IV please.

00:25:15.848 --> 00:25:17.932
- Okay. - Let's get you on an IV first.

00:25:17.933 --> 00:25:19.517
Okay.

00:25:19.518 --> 00:25:23.272
Goodness gracious me, this is torture.

00:25:36.785 --> 00:25:39.996
I'm Lee Hwayeong, an ER doctor from Samjeong Hospital.

00:25:39.997 --> 00:25:42.207
I'd like to offer my assistance if you don't mind.

00:25:44.668 --> 00:25:47.545
We should sort the patients by their symptoms first.

00:25:47.546 --> 00:25:49.964
Even if they got ill from the same food,

00:25:49.965 --> 00:25:51.883
We can't give them the same prescription.

00:25:55.345 --> 00:25:57.180
We'll be sorting the patients now.

00:25:57.181 --> 00:26:00.600
People with uneasy stomachs, people experiencing dehydration,

00:26:00.601 --> 00:26:02.352
And those with stomach pain.

00:26:04.438 --> 00:26:06.522
It hurts a bit there.

00:26:06.523 --> 00:26:08.734
- But it's not a sharp pain, is it? - No.

00:26:10.194 --> 00:26:12.696
You said you had diarrhea. Are you also running a fever?

00:26:13.697 --> 00:26:15.656
Let me take a look at you, sir.

00:26:15.657 --> 00:26:17.701
Could you lift up your shirt a little?

00:26:20.245 --> 00:26:22.414
Please clench your fist for me.

00:26:24.958 --> 00:26:27.210
Anyone here experiencing abdominal pain?

00:26:27.211 --> 00:26:28.795
Anyone having diarrhea?

00:26:28.796 --> 00:26:31.632
-  How does this feel? - Do you have abdominal pain?

00:26:36.970 --> 00:26:40.473
The nausea will go away soon, but the diarrhea will last a few days.

00:26:40.474 --> 00:26:43.644
- I'll prescribe you medicine for both. - Okay.

00:26:48.023 --> 00:26:50.859
Three times a day for five days. Make sure you take all of them.

00:26:54.404 --> 00:26:55.988
Your abdominal pain's mostly gone?

00:26:55.989 --> 00:26:57.073
- Yes. - Right.

00:26:57.074 --> 00:26:59.368
So you're feeling nauseous, and you have a migraine.

00:27:01.662 --> 00:27:03.371
This should be fine.

00:27:03.372 --> 00:27:06.959
But if your symptoms get worse, be sure to visit a hospital.

00:27:22.140 --> 00:27:24.434
- Drink lots of water, okay? - Thank you.

00:27:28.313 --> 00:27:30.107
Wow.

00:27:33.861 --> 00:27:39.323
Oh, gosh, things could have really turned ugly had it not been for you, doctor.

00:27:39.324 --> 00:27:43.411
When those patients started flooding in, I was in full-blown panic mode.

00:27:43.412 --> 00:27:44.954
I don't know how to thank you.

00:27:44.955 --> 00:27:47.457
Please don't mention it. I'm just glad I could help.

00:27:49.585 --> 00:27:51.128
I'm going to go upstairs now.

00:27:55.048 --> 00:27:56.383
Can I get something to eat?

00:27:57.968 --> 00:27:59.803
I haven't had anything to eat all day.

00:28:02.264 --> 00:28:04.474
Let's eat. I'm starving.

00:28:13.859 --> 00:28:15.903
I'm going to my room now. Good work, everyone.

00:28:27.247 --> 00:28:28.873
- Let's eat. - Let's eat.

00:28:28.874 --> 00:28:30.124
- Let's eat. - Mmm.

00:28:30.125 --> 00:28:32.668
Sounds good. Le-Let's eat. Let's eat.

00:28:32.669 --> 00:28:34.211
You haven't eaten all day.

00:28:34.212 --> 00:28:37.381
Let's go outside. Let's go eat at Cliffside.

00:28:37.382 --> 00:28:38.466
Cliffside?

00:28:38.467 --> 00:28:39.760
S-Sounds good. :cue

00:28:48.226 --> 00:28:49.310
Mmm!

00:28:49.311 --> 00:28:52.146
The food here is delicious. Wow!

00:28:52.147 --> 00:28:53.814
I'm glad you like it.

00:28:53.815 --> 00:28:56.275
I was worried it might not be to your liking,

00:28:56.276 --> 00:28:59.612
Since you're from the city and all.

00:28:59.613 --> 00:29:04.034
By the way, how do you know Dr. Do

00:29:05.285 --> 00:29:07.745
Oh, I was just curious.

00:29:07.746 --> 00:29:09.872
Since you came all this way, you seem close,

00:29:09.873 --> 00:29:13.751
But at the same time you don't seem that close.

00:29:14.836 --> 00:29:16.964
-  Stop it. - Jiui and I

00:29:19.675 --> 00:29:22.051
Used to date in university for about five years.

00:29:22.052 --> 00:29:24.638
- Huh? -  Five years?

00:29:25.138 --> 00:29:28.307
Oh, five years go by in a flash. It's nothing, really.

00:29:28.308 --> 00:29:30.810
I've never even dated someone for five whole years.

00:29:30.811 --> 00:29:33.020
Would you just She's right here.

00:29:33.021 --> 00:29:34.981
Uh, oh, oh.

00:29:34.982 --> 00:29:38.526
So you only dated for five years, huh?

00:29:38.527 --> 00:29:39.860
I see.

00:29:39.861 --> 00:29:42.196
That's when you're still young and naive.

00:29:42.197 --> 00:29:44.825
Yeah, college kids are practically babies.

00:29:46.326 --> 00:29:50.122
I felt like I had to come here when I saw Jiui on the news.

00:29:50.998 --> 00:29:52.791
I know Jiui better than anyone else.

00:29:54.167 --> 00:29:56.627
-  Let's see now. -  Au-Auntie, what is that?

00:29:56.628 --> 00:30:00.172
Oh, I was going to ask you to get these to Dr. Do Jiui.

00:30:00.173 --> 00:30:03.718
You know what they say about how an aching heart feeds off hunger.

00:30:03.719 --> 00:30:06.095
In times like this, we should just keep feeding him.

00:30:06.096 --> 00:30:07.680
-  Give it to me. - Uh-huh.

00:30:07.681 --> 00:30:09.141
I'll get it to--

00:30:10.517 --> 00:30:12.060
You should give it to him, Ms. Yuk.

00:30:12.853 --> 00:30:13.936
What?

00:30:13.937 --> 00:30:17.774
You're the one Dr. Do needs most right now.

00:30:19.192 --> 00:30:20.651
Right.

00:30:20.652 --> 00:30:23.529
Oh, you're right. Ms. Hari should go.

00:30:23.530 --> 00:30:26.907
It's not like we'd be of any use to him in this situation, right?

00:30:26.908 --> 00:30:30.411
- You should hurry or it'll get cold. -  Go make sure he eats it.

00:30:30.412 --> 00:30:32.705
- I-I'll be going then. -  Right.

00:30:32.706 --> 00:30:34.540
Get it to him before it gets cold, okay?

00:30:34.541 --> 00:30:36.626
- Thanks, Auntie. - Here you go.

00:30:40.547 --> 00:30:42.214
Thank you for your help today.

00:30:42.215 --> 00:30:44.134
Yes, of course. Mmm.

00:30:45.093 --> 00:30:47.054
Mmm. There she goes.

00:30:57.731 --> 00:30:58.940
Ms. Yuk.

00:30:59.608 --> 00:31:00.901
Huh?

00:31:05.447 --> 00:31:09.742
If you really are the person Jiui needs most right now,

00:31:09.743 --> 00:31:13.580
Please convince him to leave this island.

00:31:14.289 --> 00:31:15.372
What?

00:31:15.373 --> 00:31:17.541
I've looked into it,

00:31:17.542 --> 00:31:20.503
And there's a way for PH docs to be transferred.

00:31:20.504 --> 00:31:23.298
- Jiui can get out of this-- - What do you mean by that?

00:31:24.216 --> 00:31:27.219
Why should he have to leave? He did nothing wrong.

00:31:28.011 --> 00:31:30.138
I didn't mean that he did something wrong.

00:31:31.473 --> 00:31:33.808
I'm sure you've seen it for yourself.

00:31:33.809 --> 00:31:35.060
Jiui's really struggling.

00:31:36.812 --> 00:31:41.148
Living here must have been hell for Jiui.

00:31:41.149 --> 00:31:44.444
It must have reminded him of Seonu, and he must have blamed himself.

00:31:45.987 --> 00:31:47.405
Seonu?

00:31:49.783 --> 00:31:50.784
Oh.

00:31:52.077 --> 00:31:56.623
Then I guess you have no idea why an island would be hell for Jiui.

00:32:02.170 --> 00:32:03.797
- Jiui-- - I think

00:32:06.133 --> 00:32:08.802
I'd rather hear it directly from him.

00:32:11.555 --> 00:32:13.056
I'll be going now.

00:32:50.427 --> 00:32:55.056
Then I guess you have no idea why an island would be hell for Jiui. :cue

00:33:20.248 --> 00:33:24.085
I guess Ms. Hari had to just leave it here.

00:33:27.130 --> 00:33:28.631
I get it, though.

00:33:28.632 --> 00:33:31.133
I have no idea how we should console him either,

00:33:31.134 --> 00:33:33.929
Since he's shut the door on us like this.

00:33:38.850 --> 00:33:39.851
Dr. Do Jiui.

00:33:42.145 --> 00:33:43.146
Dr. Do Jiui!

00:33:53.740 --> 00:33:54.908
What is it?

00:33:55.492 --> 00:33:56.660
You should eat.

00:34:01.665 --> 00:34:03.291
I'll eat later.

00:34:06.670 --> 00:34:08.004
Eat right now.

00:34:08.672 --> 00:34:10.382
Everyone's worried about you.

00:34:16.638 --> 00:34:19.556
DON'T SKIP YOUR MEALS, DR. DO

00:34:36.408 --> 00:34:38.367
Hurry up and dig in.

00:34:38.368 --> 00:34:39.911
It's seasoned perfectly today.

00:34:44.165 --> 00:34:47.294
I'm sorry to put you all through this.

00:34:49.838 --> 00:34:52.966
Please don't beat yourself up too much over it, Dr. Do.

00:34:54.259 --> 00:34:57.345
You were only trying to save a patient.

00:35:03.143 --> 00:35:06.229
Anyone would have made the same call.

00:35:14.029 --> 00:35:15.030
Do you really

00:35:18.450 --> 00:35:19.451
Think so?

00:35:26.333 --> 00:35:27.334
These days

00:35:30.045 --> 00:35:31.671
I'm so scared of being a doctor.

00:35:35.717 --> 00:35:37.218
I'm so clueless about everything

00:35:39.054 --> 00:35:40.555
And I still have so much to learn,

00:35:43.141 --> 00:35:44.559
So the fact that so many lives

00:35:46.770 --> 00:35:48.980
Depend on the decisions I make

00:35:54.110 --> 00:35:55.111
Really scares me.

00:36:00.784 --> 00:36:05.372
Did you both dream of becoming doctors right from the start?

00:36:11.544 --> 00:36:15.965
To be honest, I only became a doctor because everyone said I should.

00:36:16.966 --> 00:36:20.553
Because they said studying hard and becoming a doctor was the dream.

00:36:21.930 --> 00:36:27.102
So I studied like my life depended on it, and one day, before I knew it

00:36:29.270 --> 00:36:31.523
People called me "doctor."

00:36:33.400 --> 00:36:35.694
I suddenly had to start treating patients.

00:36:37.070 --> 00:36:43.868
Man, I was so nervous my hands were shaking like crazy, you know?

00:36:48.206 --> 00:36:49.416
I'm sure it's

00:36:51.668 --> 00:36:53.837
The same for everyone here.

00:36:57.340 --> 00:36:58.591
You too, Dr. Hyeon?

00:37:00.051 --> 00:37:02.261
It didn't seem like it.

00:37:02.262 --> 00:37:04.013
I get scared every time.

00:37:05.390 --> 00:37:09.018
Sometimes, I just want to hide.

00:37:31.583 --> 00:37:32.917
:cue

