00:44:05.393 --> 00:44:07.310
Is everything working properly?

00:44:07.311 --> 00:44:08.855
Was there a reason you did that?

00:44:09.814 --> 00:44:12.108
Oh, yes. Uh-huh.

00:44:13.818 --> 00:44:16.111
- Lighting issues at the helipads? -  I understand.

00:44:16.112 --> 00:44:17.195
Thank you.

00:44:17.196 --> 00:44:20.448
So the Yujae Health Center has stopped using medical helicopters?

00:44:20.449 --> 00:44:23.994
If the lighting isn't finished yet, that would impede landings and takeoffs.

00:44:23.995 --> 00:44:26.204
- Have they wrapped up construction there? - I see.

00:44:26.205 --> 00:44:27.455
They suspended it?

00:44:27.456 --> 00:44:29.667
So you're not using the helipad at all?

00:44:30.585 --> 00:44:32.879
Uh. I understand. Okay.

00:44:57.236 --> 00:44:58.237
Oh, my.

00:45:01.824 --> 00:45:06.954
You two catch up. I'm going to go to the supermarket.

00:45:16.339 --> 00:45:17.590
Thanks for coming.

00:45:19.467 --> 00:45:21.636
I knew you'd keep waiting until I came out.

00:45:23.304 --> 00:45:24.847
But I'm not here to hear you out.

00:45:27.225 --> 00:45:28.851
I'm here to tell you about me.

00:45:33.648 --> 00:45:37.235
I tried so hard to get past what you said about how we didn't deserve to be happy.

00:45:38.903 --> 00:45:40.404
Though it felt unfair to Seonu.

00:45:42.657 --> 00:45:43.658
But

00:45:45.660 --> 00:45:47.370
I just couldn't do it.

00:45:49.705 --> 00:45:51.249
I think you were right.

00:45:52.416 --> 00:45:53.793
We don't deserve to be happy.

00:45:56.504 --> 00:45:59.048
So I don't need your consolation now, after all this time.

00:46:05.763 --> 00:46:07.640
I won't leave you by yourself this time.

00:46:12.186 --> 00:46:13.479
I looked into it.

00:46:14.272 --> 00:46:16.731
PH docs can also get transferred to a different station

00:46:16.732 --> 00:46:18.275
If they have a valid reason.

00:46:18.276 --> 00:46:22.613
If we were to get Gangseok to explain your condition to the county office,

00:46:23.531 --> 00:46:24.657
You can get transferred.

00:46:28.661 --> 00:46:31.414
Come with me, Jiui.

00:46:36.877 --> 00:46:38.087
Will leaving this place

00:46:43.259 --> 00:46:44.802
Help me forget Seonu? :cue

00:47:08.159 --> 00:47:10.828
Why didn't we think of that in the first place?

00:47:11.329 --> 00:47:14.832
It was pitch black out there because they hadn't set up the lighting,

00:47:15.666 --> 00:47:17.709
And they let Dr. Do take the fall for it

00:47:17.710 --> 00:47:19.754
To hide their shoddy construction work.

00:47:20.504 --> 00:47:23.799
I'm going to bring this up and make them take full responsibility.

00:47:25.676 --> 00:47:28.137
- Don't do it. - What?

00:47:30.348 --> 00:47:33.266
I'll do it.

00:47:33.267 --> 00:47:35.352
I'm a PH doc who's only here for a year.

00:47:35.353 --> 00:47:38.189
But no good will come of you making an enemy of Yeopoong-gun.

00:47:40.566 --> 00:47:45.446
The chief told me that you might be staying on this island for a long time.

00:47:47.698 --> 00:47:48.782
Oh.

00:47:51.827 --> 00:47:53.037
Please let me do it.

00:47:54.538 --> 00:47:57.208
Since it's a PH doc matter, let a PH doc handle it.

00:48:17.144 --> 00:48:19.480
What are you waiting for? Hurry up and go tell him.

00:48:42.378 --> 00:48:43.837
Dr. Do!

00:48:47.133 --> 00:48:48.134
Ms. Yuk.

00:48:49.135 --> 00:48:50.219
The helicopter crash

00:48:51.303 --> 00:48:54.598
It was caused by Yeopoong-gun's reckless helipad construction projects.

00:48:55.599 --> 00:48:57.725
I looked into it all day today,

00:48:57.726 --> 00:49:01.312
And apparently, out of the 20 new helipads they built,

00:49:01.313 --> 00:49:03.023
Only three had functioning lights.

00:49:03.732 --> 00:49:05.525
The lighting issue was also the reason

00:49:05.526 --> 00:49:07.777
None of the CCTVs caught what happened.

00:49:07.778 --> 00:49:09.737
So what I mean to say is

00:49:15.953 --> 00:49:18.706
The accident wasn't your fault, Dr. Do.

00:49:22.668 --> 00:49:24.712
You need to know that.

00:49:26.464 --> 00:49:28.299
That it wasn't your fault.

00:49:33.012 --> 00:49:35.556
It wasn't your fault, Dr. Do.

00:49:41.061 --> 00:49:42.730
Is that why you

00:49:44.648 --> 00:49:47.151
Kept visiting all those islands? You did it for me?

00:49:51.363 --> 00:49:53.240
So please stop hiding.

00:49:56.202 --> 00:50:00.331
I can't be by your side if you keep hiding like that.

00:50:29.151 --> 00:50:30.694
I'll stop hiding now. :cue

00:51:26.542 --> 00:51:28.876
Ta-da.

00:51:55.613 --> 00:51:56.988
Ms. Eom.

00:51:56.989 --> 00:51:57.990
Is it too much?

00:51:59.575 --> 00:52:00.992
Yes, it is too much.

00:52:02.911 --> 00:52:05.121
It's too much because you look so pretty!

00:52:05.122 --> 00:52:06.789
Ah!

00:52:06.790 --> 00:52:09.376
Here are some flowers I brought for you.

00:52:13.756 --> 00:52:15.341
Thank you.

00:52:16.425 --> 00:52:18.885
I don't know if I put on weight or something,

00:52:18.886 --> 00:52:20.845
But doesn't it look a bit tight on me?

00:52:20.846 --> 00:52:23.264
Tight? Not at all.

00:52:23.265 --> 00:52:25.600
You look so pretty. You look like an angel.

00:52:25.601 --> 00:52:27.144
Come on.

00:52:29.772 --> 00:52:31.939
Our ferry will be leaving soon. Let's go.

00:52:31.940 --> 00:52:33.192
- Come on. - Let's go.

00:52:42.826 --> 00:52:44.243
Dr. Do!

00:52:44.244 --> 00:52:47.747
Hey, what are you doing here on a weekend?

00:52:47.748 --> 00:52:50.834
I brought this so we can have it together.

00:53:03.514 --> 00:53:07.141
I was really craving pasta when I woke up this morning,

00:53:07.142 --> 00:53:11.854
But I made too much since I'm used to making two servings.

00:53:11.855 --> 00:53:13.691
Dig in.

00:53:15.067 --> 00:53:16.944
This used to be my grandma's favorite.

00:53:17.611 --> 00:53:18.612
Thanks for this.

00:53:26.370 --> 00:53:27.996
- Delicious, isn't it? - Mm-hmm.

00:53:30.624 --> 00:53:33.918
That's right, Dr. Chiyeon said he filed a request at the county office

00:53:33.919 --> 00:53:37.255
And demanded corrections from the outlets that published those articles.

00:53:37.256 --> 00:53:40.008
- Ah. - They'll publish correction articles soon.

00:53:42.553 --> 00:53:43.846
This isn't over yet.

00:53:44.471 --> 00:53:46.472
I'll keep an eye on them till the very end.

00:53:46.473 --> 00:53:49.518
We have to make sure everyone gives a proper apology.

00:53:52.980 --> 00:53:54.480
This is good enough for me.

00:53:56.775 --> 00:53:58.444
Eat up. The noodles will get mushy. :cue

00:54:06.410 --> 00:54:07.453
Excuse me.

00:54:23.719 --> 00:54:27.097
How can they charge so much for one meal?

00:54:29.224 --> 00:54:31.893
Would you mind if I ordered for us?

00:54:31.894 --> 00:54:34.730
I've actually read up on their best dishes in advance.

00:54:35.522 --> 00:54:36.565
Sure.

00:54:37.608 --> 00:54:39.525
We'd like the A course

00:54:39.526 --> 00:54:43.279
With a medium tenderloin and some caviar on the side, please.

00:54:43.280 --> 00:54:44.363
Okay.

00:54:44.364 --> 00:54:45.407
Would you like some wine?

00:54:47.493 --> 00:54:49.036
How much is

00:54:49.953 --> 00:54:51.871
Do you have Château de Lune d'Or?

00:54:51.872 --> 00:54:53.122
Yes, we do.

00:54:53.123 --> 00:54:57.585
We'd like that, and the jamón charcuterie board as well.

00:54:57.586 --> 00:54:58.878
What grade is the jamón?

00:54:58.879 --> 00:55:00.631
It's 100% Ibérico de Bellota.

00:55:01.632 --> 00:55:03.466
Sounds great. That'll be all.

00:55:03.467 --> 00:55:05.135
Yes, sir. Right away.

00:55:09.973 --> 00:55:12.351
You're so pretty today.

00:55:15.145 --> 00:55:17.814
I get it, so please stop saying that.

00:55:18.398 --> 00:55:21.276
But you really do look super pretty today.

00:55:28.200 --> 00:55:29.201
Thank you.

00:55:34.331 --> 00:55:35.332
Enjoy your meal.

00:55:38.293 --> 00:55:41.755
At these prices, you'd expect a bigger portion.

00:55:46.385 --> 00:55:47.427
Try this.

00:55:48.679 --> 00:55:50.556
Didn't we order the same dish?

00:55:51.682 --> 00:55:52.683
You're right.

00:55:53.392 --> 00:55:56.144
But it tastes better when we feed it to each other like this.

00:55:57.104 --> 00:55:58.521
You're so cheesy.

00:55:58.522 --> 00:56:01.023
Being cheesy's what dating's all about.

00:56:01.024 --> 00:56:02.108
Here, say "ah."

00:56:02.109 --> 00:56:03.443
Ah.

00:56:07.864 --> 00:56:08.948
How do you like it?

00:56:08.949 --> 00:56:09.992
Delicious, isn't it?

00:56:18.917 --> 00:56:21.461
- You can order more if you'd like. - Mmm.

00:56:27.551 --> 00:56:29.136
Seriously?

00:56:30.345 --> 00:56:31.513
What's wrong?

00:56:32.556 --> 00:56:36.517
The others got to enjoy getting stranded due to terrible weather.

00:56:36.518 --> 00:56:39.979
It's so unfair that we should get such clear skies during our visit.

00:56:39.980 --> 00:56:41.607
Of all the things to complain about.

00:56:42.816 --> 00:56:45.860
Dr. Yong, would you mind waiting here for a short while?

00:56:45.861 --> 00:56:46.944
What for?

00:56:46.945 --> 00:56:51.283
Maybe it's because of the tight clothes, but I've been feeling stuffy all day.

00:56:52.367 --> 00:56:55.202
So I'm just going to grab some antacids at a pharmacy.

00:56:55.203 --> 00:56:57.413
Mmm. Let me bring you one.

00:56:57.414 --> 00:56:59.206
I'm not a baby, okay?

00:56:59.207 --> 00:57:01.501
Hold this for me. I'll be right back.

00:57:04.129 --> 00:57:05.839
- Don't take too long. - Okay.

00:57:12.638 --> 00:57:14.764
I'd like some antacids, please.

00:57:14.765 --> 00:57:15.766
Okay.

00:57:23.273 --> 00:57:24.816
- That'll be 4,100 won. - Okay.

00:57:30.072 --> 00:57:31.073
Here you go.

00:57:42.125 --> 00:57:44.794
The ship bound for Pyeondongdo, Pyeondongdo is now departing.

00:57:44.795 --> 00:57:46.505
What's taking her so long?

00:57:47.089 --> 00:57:49.424
We'll miss the last ferry at this rate.

00:57:50.926 --> 00:57:52.677
I guess that might be even better.

00:57:55.806 --> 00:57:58.182
Uh.

00:58:31.174 --> 00:58:32.842
I'm late.

00:58:32.843 --> 00:58:34.511
Oh, man

00:58:36.638 --> 00:58:37.847
Dr. Yong!

00:58:37.848 --> 00:58:39.056
Ms. Eom!

00:58:39.057 --> 00:58:40.850
Why weren't you picking up?

00:58:40.851 --> 00:58:42.727
I'm sorry. I had to go to the bathroom.

00:58:42.728 --> 00:58:43.979
Okay. Let's hurry. :cue

00:59:10.630 --> 00:59:12.340
Are you all right?

00:59:15.385 --> 00:59:16.511
I'm sorry.

00:59:17.179 --> 00:59:20.473
I'm sure my sudden leave must have put a lot of strain on everyone.

00:59:20.474 --> 00:59:23.350
Come on, things like this happen out of the blue all the time.

00:59:23.351 --> 00:59:24.895
Don't let it get to you.

00:59:32.652 --> 00:59:36.448
By the way, shouldn't those articles have come out by now?

00:59:37.824 --> 00:59:40.826
You're sure you told the county office,

00:59:40.827 --> 00:59:43.830
The Ministry of Health and Welfare, and the reporters, right?

00:59:46.750 --> 00:59:47.793
Yes.

00:59:48.460 --> 00:59:51.129
Then why haven't we heard a peep from them?

00:59:51.755 --> 00:59:56.050
I mean, they were all up in arms when they were trying to ruin someone's life,

00:59:56.051 --> 00:59:58.594
But they sure don't seem very interested in the truth.

00:59:58.595 --> 01:00:00.222
So frustrating.

01:00:04.601 --> 01:00:06.645
When are they going to come out anyway?

01:00:07.437 --> 01:00:10.898
PYEONDONGDO HELICOPTER PH DOC

01:00:12.275 --> 01:00:14.486
- It's out! -  Where?

01:00:18.198 --> 01:00:22.117
"Health Center PH doc at Pyeondong where helicopter crash occurred

01:00:22.118 --> 01:00:25.037
Revealed to have been taking psychiatric medication"?

01:00:32.587 --> 01:00:34.088
"It has recently come to light

01:00:34.089 --> 01:00:36.632
That the PH doc stationed at Pyeondong Health Center,

01:00:36.633 --> 01:00:38.884
The recent site of a fatal helicopter crash,

01:00:38.885 --> 01:00:42.054
Had a history of receiving psychiatric treatment and medication."

01:00:42.055 --> 01:00:44.390
"This has raised concerns that the misdiagnosis

01:00:44.391 --> 01:00:48.143
May have been caused by a lapse in judgment

01:00:48.144 --> 01:00:50.146
Due to the medication he is taking."

01:00:51.565 --> 01:00:54.233
"In response, Choi Hyangmi, the director of public health,

01:00:54.234 --> 01:00:58.237
Has stated that she will be putting the PH doc taking psychiatric medication

01:00:58.238 --> 01:01:01.157
On standby and consider removing him from his post."

01:01:02.033 --> 01:01:03.117
What the hell?

01:01:03.118 --> 01:01:07.664
So they've resorted to spreading fake news just to shirk the blame now?

01:01:08.373 --> 01:01:10.165
What the heck are they talking about?

01:01:10.166 --> 01:01:12.168
What's this about a PH doc on medication?

01:01:18.091 --> 01:01:19.426
It's all true.

01:01:26.057 --> 01:01:27.267
Let me look into this.

01:01:27.893 --> 01:01:29.227
No, Dr. Hyeon.

01:01:29.811 --> 01:01:31.605
- But still, we should at least-- - Just don't!

01:01:32.814 --> 01:01:33.899
I'm okay.

01:01:53.335 --> 01:01:54.585
Oh, gosh

01:01:54.586 --> 01:01:56.003
How could something like this

01:02:05.931 --> 01:02:09.224
Those meds can cause side effects like memory loss, dizziness,

01:02:09.225 --> 01:02:10.643
And hallucinations

01:02:10.644 --> 01:02:13.979
It is a horrific incident caused by a public health doctor's misdiagnosis. :cue

01:02:13.980 --> 01:02:16.732
Appendicitis is often tricky to diagnose.

01:02:16.733 --> 01:02:18.984
If we explain your condition to the county office

01:02:18.985 --> 01:02:20.694
How dare you come here!

01:02:20.695 --> 01:02:21.738
How dare you!

01:02:27.243 --> 01:02:28.370
Dr. Do.

01:02:40.090 --> 01:02:41.299
Dr. Do, are you okay?

01:02:45.637 --> 01:02:47.596
Don't worry about a thing.

01:02:47.597 --> 01:02:49.891
I'm going to prove that those meds

01:02:51.059 --> 01:02:55.271
Had nothing to do with your diagnosis, okay?

01:02:59.651 --> 01:03:04.322
I can't take this anymore.

01:03:09.869 --> 01:03:11.871
I'm so scared of being on an island.

01:04:26.821 --> 01:04:29.531
I CAN'T BE BY YOUR SIDE

01:04:29.532 --> 01:04:36.081
IF YOU KEEP HIDING LIKE THAT

01:04:49.427 --> 01:04:52.806
PICK THE CUTIE PIE HERE

01:04:53.389 --> 01:04:56.892
CUTIE PIE? WERE YOU LOOKING FOR ME?

01:04:56.893 --> 01:05:00.814
IN ONE TAKE WITH NO BLOOPERS?

01:05:04.901 --> 01:05:07.821
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

01:05:08.571 --> 01:05:11.448
Do you really think leaving the island will help him recover?

01:05:11.449 --> 01:05:14.493
Jiui. You might actually have to step down as a doctor for good.

01:05:14.494 --> 01:05:16.286
It just sounds a bit selfish.

01:05:16.287 --> 01:05:19.331
The only way to treat unbearable pain is to run away from it.

01:05:19.332 --> 01:05:21.166
You must have struggled so much here,

01:05:21.167 --> 01:05:22.960
Surrounded on all sides by the ocean.

01:05:22.961 --> 01:05:26.380
Surrounded or not, I wanted to hang in there because I had you, Ms. Yuk.

01:05:26.381 --> 01:05:29.341
Looks like we just keep having to apologize to each other.

01:05:29.342 --> 01:05:31.427
That's why Jiui wants to leave.

01:05:32.428 --> 01:05:33.847
It's because he wants to live.

01:05:37.851 --> 01:05:39.853
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park

